"{\"uid\": \"nationalaccordnewspaper.com-botswana-declares-half-day-holiday-to-celebrate-first-olympic-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"National Accord Newspaper  Botswana's athlete Letsile Tebogo    Botswana has declared half-day public holiday to celebrate its first-ever Olympic gold medal, following athlete Letsile Tebogo's victory.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999991867042478, \"rank\": 8.132964594691817e-07, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gold medal was won at the men's 200m sprint final at the ongoing 2024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Botswanan President Mokgweetsi Masisi announced to the nation that he has found it a fitting tribute to Tebogo, \\\"Botswana's Sensation,\\\" to grant Batswana and residents an afternoon off on this very day.\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mokgweetsi Masisi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\"}, {\"begin\": 407, \"end\": 415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999991867042478, \"rank\": 8.132964594691817e-07, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 418, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carnival_Sensation\", \"score\": 0.8774521752750707, \"rank\": 0.13955503114453435, \"text\": \"Sensation\", \"types\": [\"Q11446\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carnival_Sensation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carnival_Sensation\"}, {\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.999999999984766, \"rank\": 1.5186173821417893e-11, \"text\": \"Batswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Permanent Secretary to the President Emmah Peloetletse said in a statement released on Friday.\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The decision was made to recognise and honor Tebogo, who has become the first African to win a gold medal in the 200m event in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The statement described Tebogo's performance and achievement as \\\"markedly outstanding and deserving of the nation to celebrate him in a most unique and responsible manner that will etched in the history of the country.\\\"\", \"from\": 739, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year old athlete secured Botswana's first gold medal of the Paris Olympics by completing the 200m sprint in 19.46 seconds on Thursday.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999991867042478, \"rank\": 8.132964594691817e-07, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This marks Botswana's first Olympic gold medal, following its first-ever Olympic medal in 2012 when Nigel Amos won silver in the 800m, and the men's 4\\u00d7400 relay squad won bronze at the Tokyo 2020 Games.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1305, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999991867042478, \"rank\": 8.132964594691817e-07, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1203, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nijel_Amos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nigel Amos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nijel_Amos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nijel_Amos\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Xinhua)\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1307, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"score\": 0.9999998554046774, \"rank\": 1.3947071559451693e-07, \"text\": \"Xinhua\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xinhua_News_Agency\"}]}]}"